  "body": "- **I'm submitting a ...**\r\n\r\n  - [ ] Feature request\r\n  - [X] Bug report\r\n\r\n- **Bug Report**\r\n  - What is the current behavior?\r\n\r\nOn Trezor access wallet screen, after connecting the Trezor, Network and Derivation path categories look fine on full screen. But when you make the browser window smaller, both categories turn from the deep blue we know and love to a very bright, obnoxious blue and look glitch-y.\r\n\r\nBefore: \r\n![screenshot 89](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37165338/51055229-2022b780-1594-11e9-9508-e138c2b3ee8e.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n![screenshot 90](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37165338/51055234-244ed500-1594-11e9-8187-a68bcfe7a019.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n  - If the current behavior is a bug, please provide the steps to reproduce and if possible a minimal demo of the problem\r\n\r\nMake the browser window thinner.\r\n\r\n  - What is the expected behavior?\r\n\r\nThe categories stay the same, or change in a more intuitive way.\r\n\r\n  - What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?\r\n\r\nThe categories as-is do not make much sense, and look as if they don't work.\r\n\r\n  - Where can this be found? e.g: `/interface`, `/create-wallet`, etc.\r\n\r\nhttps://beta.myetherwallet.com/access-my-wallet under the Trezor option\r\n\r\nI don't know if it's the same for Ledger/other hardware wallets. But I only saw it on Trezor thus far.\r\n",
